## Unit Test Coverage Report: go-orca Dashboard API

This report details the necessary unit tests for the backend handlers responsible for listing and submitting workflows, ensuring compliance with requirements F1, F2, F3, and F4. The tests cover expected successful operations as well as failure scenarios, including payload validation and internal service errors.

### Prerequisites

Ensure all necessary dependencies are installed and the module structure is correct.

### Testing Commands

To run all unit tests for the API handlers and services, execute the following command from the project root directory:

```bash
go test ./... ./api/handlers_test.go
```

